This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Marisa Lynn Harry in court.  Attorney Sylvan Jaspen in court for Marisa Lynn Harry.  Attorney Dennis Murphy in court on behalf of Alexander James Geocaris for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a scheduling conference. Defense is in receipt of discovery and an offer. Defense requests a status conference to allow time to review discovery materials with her client. Court grants requests. Case is adjourned for a status conference. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Status conference scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Marisa Lynn Harry in court with Attorney Sylvan Jaspen; both appear by video.  Defendant Marisa Lynn Harry in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: South Milwaukee Lt D. Hoeppner.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 11.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 27, 2022 at 08:30 am.
State Public Defender - Order Appointing Counsel.  Received and Filed.  nk
Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 1 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.  Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Marisa Lynn Harry in court with attorney David Thomas Conley.  Defendant Marisa Lynn Harry in custody.  Michael J. Odden appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Marisa Lynn Harry appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Swanson, Branch 11.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.
